# Command Center — Agentic OS

You operate inside an Agentic OS rooted at this directory (`$AGENT_ROOT`).
The human supervisor watches your work through a three-pane dashboard:
goals on the left, live terminal in the middle, the living `plan.md` on
the right.

## Filesystem contract

- `/memory/user.md` — personal preferences; read at session start.
- `/memory/brand_context/` — `voice.md`, `icp.md`, `positioning.md`.
  Consult before writing any external-facing copy.
- `/projects/<slug>/plan.md` — the SINGLE source of truth for the active goal.
- `/projects/<slug>/state.json` — status metadata; do not edit unless asked.
- `/skills/*.md` — reusable procedures. Prefer these over inventing new ones.
- `/review/` — drop files here to request human approval, then STOP.

The environment variable `CLAUDE_PROJECT` names the active project slug.
The environment variable `AGENT_ROOT` is this directory.

## Living-plan protocol

On every meaningful step (decision, code change, new blocker), rewrite
`/projects/$CLAUDE_PROJECT/plan.md` with these sections, in this order:

```
## Objective
## Status           (one of: Discovery, Executing, Blocked, Awaiting Review, Done)
## Next Actions     (checkbox list, top-of-mind first)
## Decisions Log    (append-only, timestamped as YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM)
## Open Questions
```

Keep `plan.md` terse — the supervisor reads it in a side pane, not a doc viewer.

## Human-in-the-loop

When you need supervisor approval, write a file to:

    /review/<ISO-timestamp>-<short-topic>.md

containing:
1. What you did.
2. What you need decided.
3. Options (with your recommendation).

Then pause and wait for the supervisor to respond (they will edit the file
or send instructions via the terminal).

## Boundaries

- Never touch files outside `$AGENT_ROOT`.
- Never call external APIs for tasks the local CLI can perform.
- Prefer reading `/skills/*.md` before inventing a new procedure.
- When in doubt, ask — don't assume.
